summary: 'X-Men' and 'Fantastic Four' could join the Marvel Cinematic Universe in early 2019
title: 'X-Men' and 'Fantastic Four' could join the Marvel Cinematic Universe in early 2019
body:
It sounds like the planned convergence of the X-Men and the Fantastic Four into the Marvel Cinematic Universe is on course, and could be happening much sooner than we thought.

Kevin Fiege, the boss of the MCU for Disney, has said that things are looking ‘very, very good’ for the merger of the comic book worlds.

As it stands, X-Men movies, Fantastic Four movies and Deadpool movies are produced by the Fox studio.

But with the upcoming merger between Fox and Disney, the home of Iron Man, The Avengers, Thor and the gang, we’ll likely soon see the crossovers on screen. Soon being key word.

“We’ve been told it’s looking very, very good and could happen in the first six months of next year,” he told Variety.

“The notion of the characters coming back is great.

“But in terms of actually thinking about it and actually planning things, we haven’t started that yet.

“It’s nice when a company that created all these characters can have access to all those characters. It only makes sense for Marvel to be supervised by one entity. There shouldn’t be two Marvels.”

So that Deadpool meets Thor movie we’ve always wanted to happen could be closer than ever.

‘Excelsior!’ as the late Stan Lee might have said.

body:
Okay, so I’m rewatch IW now that it’s on Netflix, so I decided to make a “happy things” posts

  • Father-Son bonding between Tony and Peter
  • “Kid, you’re an Avenger now.”
  • Thor and Rocket duo
  • Small, but good comedy
  • “Get this man a shield!”
  • Shuri
  • Fast boi Steve™
  • Cap’s beard
  • “Where to cap?” “Home.”
  • Peter’s new suit
  • Bruce in the ironsuit
  • Quinn and Gamora
  • Peter Quinn
  • “My movement is so slow, it’s un-preceptable”
  • “Die, blanket of death!”
  • “Dude. Your embarrassing me in front of the wizards”
  • “Where is Gamora?” “I’ll do you one better, who is Gamora?” “I’ll do you one better, why is Gamora?”
  • Just guardians meeting Tony, Peter, and Strange in general.
  • Bubble gun
  • Peter’s pop culture references
  • Thor’s new ax
  • “So have you seen this really old movie Aliens?”
  • ‘Flying donut’
  • “He never fought me.” “Yeah he has.” “Well, he’s never fought me twice.”
  • “I’m backup.” “No, you’re a stowaway. Shut up. The adults are talking.”
  • “I like your plan, except, it sucks.”
  • Rabbit
  • Kick names, take ass.
  • Peter calling out attacks as he hits Thanos
  • “I am Groot!” “I am Steve Rodgers.”
  • Tony being 100% done the whole movie.

Feel free to add on

summary: who sleeps closer to the wall/window and who is stuck sleeping on the edge of the bed? lol
question: who sleeps closer to the wall/window and who is stuck sleeping on the edge of the bed? lol
answer:
our bed is in the middle of the room, so both of us are on the edge. it was a bit of a fight at first, steve wanted the edge so he could get to his shield faster, i wanted the edge so i wouldn’t feel confined/trapped when i slept, so we decided to move the bed. 

-bucky

body:
